    • updateBorders

      private void updateBorders(Cell currentCell, Cell nextCell)
      Determines which direction the next cell will be relative to the current cell, using the (x,y) coordinates and removing the borders between by updating the 'borders[]' values of the cell object and using the Cell method, 'setBorders'.
      Parameters:
      currentCell - the current 'occupied' cell in the maze generation process
      nextCell - the randomly selected, neighbouring, unvisited cell

    • setDifficulty

      private int setDifficulty()
      Sets difficulty of maze on a 1-5 scale. Difficulty is determined by the total amount of cells and a set of predetermined ranges.
      Returns:
      integer value from 1-5, 1 being the lowest difficulty and 5 being the highest difficulty
